trans-unit.source: Python library for tries with different grades of fastness
trans-unit.target: 用于不同牢度等级的尝试的Python库。

trans-unit.source: The interfaces of the X-fast and Y-fast tries are identical, the Y-fast trie is used here as an example.
trans-unit.target: X-fast和Y-fast尝试的接口是一样的,这里以Y-fast尝试为例。

trans-unit.source: The most notable benefit of X-fast and Y-fast tries compared to more common data structures such as binary search trees is that searches are log-logarithmic in the cardinality of the universe as opposed to being logarithmic in the number of elements in the structure itself; For reference if you needed to store 2^20 items with a potential maximum value of 2^32 - 1, finding a particular item would take 20 operations in a red/black or AVL tree, but only 5 with an X-fast or Y-fast trie.
trans-unit.target: 与更常见的数据结构(如二进制搜索树)相比,X-fast和Y-fast trie最显著的好处是,搜索在宇宙的cardinality上是对数的,而不是在结构本身的元素数量上是对数的;作为参考,如果你需要存储2^20个项目,潜在的最大值是2^32-1,那么在红/黑或AVL树中寻找一个特定的项目需要20次操作,但在X-fast或Y-fast trie中只需要5次。

trans-unit.source: py-fast-trie is a package that contains pure-Python implementations of an X-fast Trie and a Y-fast trie, as described in the foundational paper.
trans-unit.target: py-fast-trie is a package that contains pure-Python implementations of an X-fast Trie and a Y-fast trie, as described in the foundational paper.
